The paper deals with timing synchronization in optical wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of OFDM, which is a common technique in communication systems (cs.COMM). Additionally, the paper focuses on optical intensity modulation and direct detection, which falls under the category of optics and photonics (cs.OH and cs.PHOTONICS).
